# Flutter architecture

## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | Location | Rules |
|-------|----------|-------|
| Domain | `domain/` | Pure Dart models, enums, value types. No Flutter imports. |
| Data | `data/` | HTTP, DB, mappers. Converts between domain and external APIs. |
| Presentation | `presentation/` | Screens, `Notifier` controllers, widgets. |

## State management

```dart
// Controller pattern used in this project
final myControllerProvider =
    NotifierProvider<MyController, MyState>(MyController.new);

class MyController extends Notifier<MyState> {
  @override
  MyState build() => MyState.initial();

  void updateSomething(String value) {
    state = state.copyWith(something: value);
  }
}
```

- Screens: `ConsumerWidget` or `ConsumerStatefulWidget`, `ref.watch` for state, `ref.read` for actions.
- Keep widgets stateless when state lives in a controller.

## Imports

```dart
// ✅ Feature widget importing its own domain
import '../../domain/http_method_type.dart';

// ✅ Shared widget from shared/
import '../../../shared/widgets/app_button.dart';

// ❌ Feature A importing Feature B's presentation
import '../../other_feature/presentation/other_screen.dart';
```

## File naming

- Screens: `*_screen.dart`
- Controllers: `*_controller.dart`, state: `*_state.dart`
- Widgets: descriptive names (`request_url_bar.dart`)
- Domain enums: `*_type.dart` or standalone noun (`auth_type.dart`)
